{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877888464,"sessionID":"ses_285700e6cffe1o1w0ORJi5ZG82","part":{"id":"prt_d7a90c199001yw3jvdFiteZGHP","messageID":"msg_d7a907aea001ibZ6zXWG21d4U3","sessionID":"ses_285700e6cffe1o1w0ORJi5ZG82","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nProvide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid token allows request\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token in the Authorization header\n- **WHEN** a request is made to a PicoD execution endpoint\n- **THEN** the middleware SHALL validate the token and allow the request to proceed\n\n#### Scenario: Missing token returns 401\n- **GIVEN** a request without an Authorization header\n- **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid token format returns 401\n- **GIVEN** a request with an Authorization header not starting with \"Bearer \"\n- **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid authorization format\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n- **GIVEN** a request with an expired JWT token\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Malformed token returns 401\n- **GIVEN** a request with a malformed JWT token\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token malformed\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n- **GIVEN** a request with a JWT token signed with wrong key\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token signature invalid\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Token Claims Extraction and Context Propagation\n\nThe system SHALL extract JWT claims and store them in the request context for downstream handlers.\n\n#### Scenario: Claims stored in context\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id claim\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n- **THEN** the extracted claims SHALL be stored in the request context\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID extracted from token\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n- **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve session_id from context\n\n#### Scenario: User ID extracted from token\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with user_id=\"user-456\"\n- **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n- **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve user_id from context\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox ID extracted from token\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with sandbox_id=\"sandbox-789\"\n- **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n- **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve sandbox_id from context\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace extracted from token\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with namespace=\"default\"\n- **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n- **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve namespace from context\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple claims extracted\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id, user_id, sandbox_id, namespace, and runtime_kind claims\n- **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n- **THEN** all claims SHALL be available in the context for downstream use\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session ID Validation Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL verify that the session_id claim is present and valid.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session_id returns 403\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token without a session_id claim\n- **WHEN** the request is processed\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id claim is required\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session_id returns 403\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with empty session_id=\"\"\n- **WHEN** the request is processed\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id cannot be empty\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID matches request parameter\n- **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/abc123\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n- **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID mismatch returns 403\n- **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/def456\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session access denied\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Optional Authentication Support\n\nThe system SHALL support optional authentication for specific endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: Optional auth allows anonymous requests\n- **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n- **WHEN** a request without a token is made\n- **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed without claims in context\n\n#### Scenario: Optional auth extracts claims when present\n- **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n- **WHEN** a request with a valid token is made\n- **THEN** the claims SHALL be extracted and stored in context\n\n#### Scenario: Optional auth ignores invalid tokens\n- **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n- **WHEN** a request with an invalid token is made\n- **THEN** the request SHALL proceed without claims (invalid token is treated as no token)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JWT Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support configurable JWT settings for the PicoD middleware.\n\n#### Scenario: Configuration from environment variables\n- **GIVEN** environment variables `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER`, `PICOD_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`, and `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY`\n- **WHEN** the middleware configuration is initialized\n- **THEN** the configuration SHALL be populated from these environment variables\n\n#### Scenario: Configuration with public key PEM\n- **GIVEN** a valid RSA public key in PEM format in configuration\n- **WHEN** the middleware validates tokens\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the configured public key to verify signatures\n\n#### Scenario: Configuration with JWKS endpoint\n- **GIVEN** a JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) endpoint URL in configuration\n- **WHEN** the middleware needs to validate tokens\n- **THEN** it SHALL fetch the public key from the JWKS endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid configuration returns error\n- **GIVEN** an invalid JWT configuration (e.g., empty issuer)\n- **WHEN** the middleware is initialized\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error\n\n#### Scenario: Default configuration values\n- **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n- **WHEN** the middleware configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** it SHALL use sensible defaults (issuer=\"picod\", expiry=5m)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Token Refresh Support\n\nThe system SHALL support token refresh for extended sessions.\n\n#### Scenario: Refresh token endpoint\n- **GIVEN** a valid refresh token\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/auth/refresh` with the refresh token\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return a new access token and refresh token pair\n\n#### Scenario: Expired refresh token returns 401\n- **GIVEN** an expired refresh token\n- **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"refresh token expired\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid refresh token returns 401\n- **GIVEN** an invalid refresh token\n- **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid refresh token\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Public Key Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose a public key endpoint for token verification by clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Get public key\n- **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with RSA keys\n- **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/.well-known/jwks.json`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return the public key in JWKS format\n\n#### Scenario: Public key includes key ID\n- **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with key versioning\n- **WHEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n- **THEN** the response SHALL include the key ID (kid) for each key\n\n#### Scenario: Public key algorithm specified\n- **GIVEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n- **WHEN** the response is returned\n- **THEN** it SHALL include the algorithm (alg: RS256) and key type (kty: RSA)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n\nThe system SHALL expose metrics for JWT middleware operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Token validation counter\n- **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n- **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validations_total` counter with labels for result (success/failure)\n\n#### Scenario: Token validation latency\n- **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n- **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validation_duration_seconds` histogram\n\n#### Scenario: Active session tracking\n- **GIVEN** tokens are being validated\n- **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n- **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_active_sessions` gauge with session_id labels\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Logging\n\nThe system SHALL implement structured logging for JWT middleware operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful authentication logged\n- **GIVEN** a request with valid token is processed\n- **WHEN** authentication succeeds\n- **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, user_id, endpoint, duration\n\n#### Scenario: Failed authentication logged\n- **GIVEN** a request with invalid token is processed\n- **WHEN** authentication fails\n- **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: error, error_code, endpoint, remote_addr\n\n#### Scenario: Token refresh logged\n- **GIVEN** a token refresh request is processed\n- **WHEN** refresh succeeds or fails\n- **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, result, duration\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling\n\nThe system SHALL provide consistent error responses for authentication failures.\n\n#### Scenario: WWW-Authenticate header on 401\n- **GIVEN** an unauthenticated request\n- **WHEN** the middleware returns HTTP 401\n- **THEN** the response SHALL include `WWW-Authenticate: Bearer` header\n\n#### Scenario: JSON error response format\n- **GIVEN** an authentication error occurs\n- **WHEN** the error response is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL be JSON with fields: error, message, code (optional)\n\n#### Scenario: Error code classification\n- **GIVEN** various authentication failures\n- **WHEN** errors are returned\n- **THEN** each SHALL have a machine-readable code: TOKEN_EXPIRED, TOKEN_INVALID, TOKEN_MALFORMED, MISSING_CLAIMS\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/picod/jwt_middleware.go` | JWT authentication middleware implementation |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt_config.go` | JWT configuration structures and loading |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt_types.go` | JWT types and context keys for PicoD |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt_handlers.go` | HTTP handlers for auth endpoints (refresh, JWKS) |\n| `pkg/picod/errors.go` | JWT and authentication error definitions |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token parsing and validation |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Local | Shared JWT types and utilities |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics collection |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Auth Required | Description |\n|--------|------|---------------|-------------|\n| POST | `/execute/{session_id}` | Yes | Execute command in sandbox |\n| GET | `/execute/{id}/status` | Yes | Get execution status |\n| GET | `/execute/{id}/output` | Yes | Stream execution output |\n| DELETE | `/execute/{id}` | Yes | Cancel execution |\n| POST | `/auth/refresh` | No | Refresh access token |\n| GET | `/.well-known/jwks.json` | No | Get public keys in JWKS format |\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router` | Reuses JWTManager for token validation; imports TokenClaims type |\n| `pkg/picod/executor.go` | Reads session_id from context to validate execution requests |\n| `pkg/store` | May store refresh token metadata for revocation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager` | Coordinates JWT configuration across components |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The PicoD JWT middleware leverages the existing `pkg/router` JWT implementation where possible\n- Token claims must include `session_id` for all PicoD execution endpoints\n- The middleware supports both mandatory and optional authentication patterns\n- Public keys are exposed via JWKS endpoint for external verification\n- Metrics are prefixed with `picod_` to distinguish from router metrics\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"},{"range":{"start":{"line":35,"character":31},"end":{"line":35,"character":42}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/google/uuid should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/status.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":65,"character":37},"end":{"line":65,"character":40}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"},{"range":{"start":{"line":74,"character":43},"end":{"line":74,"character":46}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"},{"range":{"start":{"line":122,"character":26},"end":{"line":122,"character":29}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/types.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":145,"character":20},"end":{"line":145,"character":31}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/validation.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":75,"character":5},"end":{"line":75,"character":19}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"function \"isValidCommand\" is unused","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/picod/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt_types.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":130,"character":25},"end":{"line":130,"character":36}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":243,"character":33},"end":{"line":243,"character":44}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":246,"character":37},"end":{"line":246,"character":48}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":41,"character":1},"end":{"line":41,"character":11}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"const \"rsaKeySize\" is unused","tags":[1]},{"range":{"start":{"line":42,"character":1},"end":{"line":42,"c