{"type":"text","timestamp":1775877902352,"sessionID":"ses_285700e6cffe1o1w0ORJi5ZG82","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9239e7001Rtj6G4lD2WWrRN","messageID":"msg_d7a921a030013XdPc0gAI43CjI","sessionID":"ses_285700e6cffe1o1w0ORJi5ZG82","type":"text","text":"I've written the `delta-spec.md` file for AR-017 PicoD JWT middleware. The spec follows the OpenSpec format with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios covering:\n\n**Requirements:**\n1. **JWT Token Validation Middleware** - Validates tokens, handles missing/invalid/expired tokens\n2. **Token Claims Extraction** - Extracts session_id, user_id, sandbox_id, namespace claims to context\n3. **Session ID Validation** - Requires session_id claim, validates session access\n4. **Optional Authentication** - Supports endpoints with optional auth\n5. **JWT Configuration** - Environment-based config, public key/JWKS support\n6. **Token Refresh** - Refresh token endpoint for extended sessions\n7. **Public Key Endpoint** - JWKS endpoint for external verification\n8. **Metrics** - Prometheus metrics for validation counts and latency\n9. **Logging** - Structured logging for auth events\n10. **Error Handling** - Consistent error responses with WWW-Authenticate headers\n\n**Key Design Decisions:**\n- Integrates with existing `pkg/router` JWT implementation\n- PicoD-specific claims (session_id is required for execution endpoints)\n- Metrics prefixed with `picod_` for differentiation\n- JWKS endpoint for public key distribution","time":{"start":1775877902350,"end":1775877902350}}}
